  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 230°C/ 210°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Chop your<strong> tomato[es] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>pepper</strong> <strong>strips</strong>, <strong>tomato wedges </strong>and <strong>garlic </strong>(skin on) to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with your <strong>ground coriander</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1646136873813-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1646136873813-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1646136873813-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1646136873813-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1646136873813-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle, then put the tray[s] in the oven for 12-15 min or until the pepper is charred</p><p>Whilst the vegetables are cooking, peel and slice your <strong>shallot[s] </strong>finely, then add the <strong>sliced shallot </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>sugar </strong>and set aside to pickle – this is your<strong> quick-pickled shallot</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper, remove 3 <strong>outer leaves</strong> per person and set aside, then shred the <strong>inner core</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1646136878651-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1646136878651-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1646136878651-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1646136878651-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1646136878651-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks, then finely chop your <strong>dill</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>bulgur wheat </strong>and<strong> </strong>your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 7-9 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1646136881959-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1646136881959-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1646136881959-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1646136881959-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1646136881959-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>cornflour</strong> with <strong>half </strong>your <strong>ground sumac </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>in a bowl</p><p>Pat your <strong>haddock bites</strong> dry with kitchen paper, then add to the bowl and give everything a good mix up until the haddock is fully coated</p><p>Tip: Unevenly sized haddock bites? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1646136885890-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1646136885890-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1646136885890-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1646136885890-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1646136885890-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated haddock bites</strong> and cook for 5-6 min, turning once half way, or until cooked through – this is your <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>sumac haddock</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1646136889003-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1646136889003-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1646136889003-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1646136889003-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1646136889003-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the haddock is cooking, add the <strong>chopped dill </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>mayo</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and mix everything together – this is your <strong>dill mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1646136893230-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1646136893230-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1646136893230-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1646136893230-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1646136893230-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables are cooked, remove the tray[s] from the oven and carefully remove the skin[s] from the <strong>roasted garlic </strong>(they will be hot!), then chop roughly</p><p>Fluff the <strong>drained bulgur</strong> with a fork</p><p>Combine the <strong>roasted vegetables</strong> and<strong> chopped</strong> <strong>roasted garlic</strong> with the <strong>cooked bulgur</strong>, then add the<strong> chopped parsley </strong>and stir everything together – this is your <strong>roasted vegetable bulgur</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1646136897856-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1646136897856-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1646136897856-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1646136897856-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1646136897856-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Load the <strong>lettuce leaves</strong> with the <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>vegetable bulgur</strong>,<strong> shredded lettuce</strong>, and the<strong> crispy sumac haddock</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>dill mayo</strong> and top with <strong>quick-pickled shallot</strong></p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>remaining ground sumac</strong> all over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
